Executive Profile
John W. Diercksen  Independent Director, Popular, Inc.AgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 6 Board Members in 6 different organizations across 8 different industries.See Board Relationships68$170,000
Background

		Mr. John W. Diercksen has been Principal of Greycrest, LLC since October 2013. Mr. Diercksen has 29 years of experience in the communications industry. He served as Senior Advisor at Liontree Investment Advisors, an investment banking firm, since April 2014. He served as an Executive Vice President at Verizon Communications Inc. from January 2013 to September 2013. He was responsible for key strategic initiatives related to the review and assessment of potential mergers, ... acquisitions and divestitures. He served as Chief Executive Officer of Beachfront Wireless LLC from December 2015 to November 2016. He served as an Executive Vice President of Strategy, Development and Planning of Verizon Communications Inc. from June 2003 to December 2012, where he was responsible for corporate strategy, mergers, acquisitions and divestitures, business development, venture investments, strategic alliances, joint ventures and strategic planning company-wide. In this capacity, he was instrumental in forging Verizon’s strategy of technology investment and repositioning its assets through the acquisition of spectrum including the cable spectrum transaction; the merger with MCI; the Alltel acquisition; the restructuring of international assets; the spinoff of Verizon’s directories unit and landline assets; and the Terremark and Cloud Switch acquisitions. He served as a Senior Vice President of Investor Relations for Verizon since July 2000 until 2003. He served as an Acting Group President of Directory for Bell Atlantic since January 2000, where he was responsible for its $2.4 billion print and online directories business in the United States and the operations of Global Directory Services in the Czech and Slovak Republics, Gibraltar, Poland, Greece and China. Prior to that, he served as Chief Financial Officer and Chief Information Officer of Bell Atlantic’s the Directory Group since 1997 and its Chief Information Officer since 1998. Mr. Diercksen joined NYNEX in 1986 and served as Vice President of Finance and Administration for its Business Information Systems Company, where he directed management processes for all Accounting, Treasury and Human Resources functions. Since 1991, he served as Vice President of Finance and Treasurer for NYNEX's Telecommunications Group and was responsible for all financial functions, regulatory compliance and resource allocation. He began his career in 1971 with the Insurance Company of North America. He joined Lever Brothers Company in New York. In 1975, he joined International Playtex's International Division as Director of International Costs and Budgets. In 1979, he joined American Can Company's Technologies Division as Director of Financial Planning and Control. In 1982, he joined Coleco Industries as Corporate Controller. Mr. Diercksen has been an Independent Director of Intelsat S.A. since September 5, 2013 and Popular, Inc. since October 1, 2013. Mr. Diercksen has been a Director of Intelsat Corporation since September 2013, Banco Popular de Puerto Rico since 2013 and Terremark Worldwide, Inc. since April 4, 2011. He served as a Director of Harman International Industries, Incorporated from June 26, 2013 to March 10, 2017. He served as a Director of Verizon Telematics, Inc. (alternate name, HUGHES Telematics, Inc.), since July 26, 2012. He served as a Director of Idearc Inc. He is an Active Member of the community, he is involved with Saint Joseph's High School, All Hallows High School, Saint Catherine's Church, Archdiocese Inner City Schools and Saint Catherine's Visiting Hospital Organizations. Mr. Diercksen holds BBA in Finance from Iona College and an MBA from Pace University and completed postgraduate work in financial management.Read Full Background




